# TypeScript Migration

This project is **gradually migrating from JavaScript to TypeScript**.

## Rules

- **All new files** must be `.ts` or `.svelte` with `<script lang="ts">`
- **When editing an existing `.js` file**, convert it to `.ts` in the same PR/commit
- **When editing a `.svelte` file** that uses plain `<script>`, add `lang="ts"` and add types
- **Never use `@ts-ignore`** — fix the type error instead
- **Never use `any`** unless it's a genuine escape hatch with a comment explaining why

## Svelte components

```svelte
<!-- ❌ OLD -->
<script>
  let { value, onchange } = $props();
</script>

<!-- ✅ NEW -->
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props {
    value: string;
    onchange: (v: string) => void;
  }
  let { value, onchange }: Props = $props();
</script>
```

## Typing $props()

Always destructure with an explicit interface:

```ts
interface Props {
  label: string;
  count?: number;
  onclick?: () => void;
}
let { label, count = 0, onclick }: Props = $props();
```

## Typing $state / $derived

```ts
let items = $state<string[]>([]);
let count = $derived<number>(items.length);
```

## Module files

```ts
// ❌ OLD — utils.js with JSDoc
/** @param {string} id */
export function getById(id) { ... }

// ✅ NEW — utils.ts
export function getById(id: string): Item | undefined { ... }
```

## Imports

Use `import type` for type-only imports:

```ts
import type { Pipeline } from '$lib/types';
import { createPipeline } from '$lib/pipeline';
```

## Shared types

Put shared interfaces/types in `src/lib/types.ts` (create if it doesn't exist).

## jsconfig.json

The `jsconfig.json` is kept for legacy JS files still being migrated. Do not delete it until all JS is converted.
